## 🔍 Overview

**T2 Communicate** is a comprehensive WhatsApp Business API platform that enables businesses to integrate WhatsApp messaging capabilities seamlessly. Our robust API provides:

### 🚀 Core Features
- **Authentication & User Management** - Secure token-based authentication
- **Multi-format Messaging** - Text, images, documents, audio, video, and templates
- **Contact & Group Management** - Organize and manage your contact database
- **Template Management** - Create, sync, and manage WhatsApp Business templates
- **Real-time Webhooks** - Get instant delivery status updates
- **Analytics & Reporting** - Track message performance and engagement
- **Broadcast Campaigns** - Send bulk messages to targeted audiences

### 🌐 Platform Information
- **Base URL:** `https://communicateapi.t2.sa/api/` ⚠️ **PRODUCTION ONLY**
- **Protocol:** HTTPS only (TLS 1.2+)
- **Authentication:** Bearer Token (JWT)
- **Data Format:** JSON

> **🚨 IMPORTANT**: Always use the production URL `https://communicateapi.t2.sa/api/` for all API calls.
> Never use mock or testing URLs in production environments.

### 📱 Supported Message Types
| Type | Description | Max Size | Formats |
|------|-------------|----------|---------|
| Text | Plain text messages with emojis | 4,096 chars | UTF-8 |
| Image | Photo messages | 5MB | JPEG, PNG |
| Document | File attachments | 100MB | PDF, DOC, XLS, PPT, etc. |
| Audio | Voice messages | 16MB | MP3, AAC, AMR |
| Video | Video messages | 16MB | MP4, 3GP |
| Templates | WhatsApp approved templates | - | Text, Media, Interactive |

## 🔐 Authentication

T2 Communicate uses JWT (JSON Web Token) based authentication to secure API access. All API requests must include a valid Bearer token in the Authorization header.

### 🔑 Getting Started

#### Step 1: Register Your Organization
Before using the API, you need to register your organization and create a user account.

#### Step 2: Obtain Access Token
Use your credentials to get an access token that will be used for all subsequent API calls.

### 🚪 Login Endpoint
**POST** `/auth/login`

Authenticate with T2 Communicate and receive an access token.

**Request Body:**
```json
{
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "password": "securepassword"
}
```

**Success Response (200):**
```json
{
    "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
    "organizationId": "org123",
    "userId": "user456",
    "expireInSeconds": 3600
}
```

**Error Response (500):**
```json
{
    "Type": 0,
    "Message": "The email or password is incorrect",
    "StatusCode": 500
}
```

### Token Usage
All authenticated requests must include the Bearer token in the Authorization header:
```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

## ⚠️ Error Handling & Status Codes

T2 Communicate uses a standardized error response structure across all API endpoints. All errors return appropriate HTTP status codes with detailed error messages.

### HTTP Status Codes
| Status Code | Description | When It Occurs |
|-------------|-------------|----------------|
| 200 | Success | Request completed successfully |
| 400 | Bad Request | Invalid request parameters or body |
| 401 | Unauthorized | Missing or invalid authentication token |
| 403 | Forbidden | User lacks permission for the operation |
| 404 | Not Found | Resource not found |
| 500 | Internal Server Error | Server-side error occurred |

### Error Response Structure

All API errors follow a consistent JSON structure:

```json
{
    "Message": "Error description",
    "StatusCode": 400,
    "InnerException": null
}
```

**Response Fields:**
- `Message` (string): Human-readable error description
- `StatusCode` (number): HTTP status code as integer
- `InnerException` (object|null): Additional error details (usually null)

### Common Error Messages

#### Authentication Errors (401/403)
- `"The email or password is incorrect"`
- `"Super admin can't login to customer portal"`
- `"You don't have access to the admin portal"`
- `"Email not found. Please try again."`
- `"Invalid or expired refresh token"`
- `"Invalid token"`

#### Resource Not Found Errors (404)
- `"This user doesn't exist {email}"`
- `"This organization does not exist {organizationId}"`
- `"This number does not exist {phoneNumber}"`
- `"Template not found"`
- `"Contact not found"`
- `"Contact group not found"`
- `"This group message doesn't exist {groupMessageId}"`

#### Validation Errors (400)
- `"Contact {name} number already exists"`
- `"Email: {email} is already exists"`
- `"Wrong password"`
- `"Passwords must match"`
- `"The PhoneNumber field is not a valid phone number"`
- `"One or more validation errors occurred"`

#### Permission Errors (403)
- `"You don't have access to this endpoint"`
- `"sorry, you need to recharge your balance"`

#### Server Errors (500)
- `"Something went wrong. Please, try again later. ({error details})"`

### Message Status Types

T2 Communicate tracks message delivery status using these standardized values:

| Status | Description | When It Occurs |
|--------|-------------|----------------|
| `Scheduled` | Message is scheduled for future delivery | When scheduling messages |
| `InProgress` | Message is being processed | During message sending |
| `Sent` | Message successfully sent to WhatsApp | WhatsApp confirms receipt |
| `Delivered` | Message delivered to recipient's device | WhatsApp delivery confirmation |
| `Read` | Message opened/read by recipient | WhatsApp read receipt |
| `Failed` | Message delivery failed | Any delivery failure |
| `FailedToUpdate` | Status update failed | Webhook update issues |

## Message APIs

### Send Custom Message
**POST** `/message/send-custom`

This is the primary endpoint for sending various types of messages to WhatsApp contacts.

#### Request Structure
```json
{
    "recipient": {
        "id": "string" // Required: Contact phone number (e.g., "201276267641")
    },
    "message": {
        "text": "string", // Optional: Message text content
        "quickReplies": [ // Optional: Quick reply buttons
            {
                "title": "string", // Required: Button text
                "contentType": "string", // Optional: Content type for media
                "payload": "string" // Optional: Button payload/URL
            }
        ]
    },
    "media": { // Optional: Media attachment
        "contentType": "string", // Required: MIME type
        "url": "string", // Required: Media URL
        "size": number, // Required: File size in bytes
        "name": "string", // Required: Original filename
        "mediaType": "string" // Required: "Image"|"File"|"Audio"|"Video"
    }
}
```

#### Response Structure
```json
{
    "id": "string", // Conversation ID
    "messageId": "string", // Unique message identifier
    "contactId": "string", // Contact ID
    "contactName": "string", // Contact display name
    "contactNumber": "string", // Contact phone number
    "unreadMessageCount": number, // Unread messages count
    "lastMessage": "string", // Last message preview
    "status": "string", // Message status: "sent"|"delivered"|"read"|"failed"
    "intials": "string", // Contact initials for avatar
    "profilePictureBackground": "string", // Avatar background color
    "senderType": "string", // "user"|"contact"
    "senderId": "string", // Sender identifier
    "lastMessageDate": "2025-08-03T12:18:39.681Z", // ISO timestamp
    "isTemplate": boolean, // Whether message uses template
    "assigneeId": "string", // Optional: Assigned agent ID
    "assigneeType": "string", // Optional: Assignment type
    "isUnSubscribed": boolean, // Contact subscription status
    "currentTicketId": "string", // Optional: Support ticket ID
    "conversationStatus": "string", // Conversation state
    "startMessageDate": "2025-08-03T12:18:39.681Z", // Conversation start time
    "media": { // Optional: Media information
        "title": "string", // Media title/filename
        "type": "string", // Media type
        "url": "string" // Media access URL
    },
    "templateData": { // Optional: Template structure data
        "header": {
            "type": "string", // "text"|"image"|"video"|"document"
            "text": "string", // Header text content
            "url": "string" // Header media URL
        },
        "body": {
            "type": "string", // Always "text"
            "text": "string", // Body text with parameters
            "url": "string" // Not used for body
        },
        "footer": {
            "type": "string", // Always "text"
            "text": "string", // Footer text
            "url": "string" // Not used for footer
        },
        "buttons": [ // Template buttons
            {
                "type": "string", // "quick_reply"|"url"|"phone_number"
                "text": "string", // Button text
                "url": "string", // URL for url buttons
                "phoneNumber": "string" // Phone for call buttons
            }
        ]
    }
}
```

#### Response Field Details

**Required Fields:**
- `id`: Always present, conversation identifier
- `messageId`: Always present, unique message ID for tracking
- `contactId`: Always present, contact identifier
- `contactNumber`: Always present, recipient phone number
- `status`: Always present, current message status
- `lastMessageDate`: Always present, timestamp of last activity

**Optional Fields:**
- `contactName`: May be null if contact has no saved name
- `assigneeId`: Only present if conversation is assigned to an agent
- `assigneeType`: Only present with assigneeId
- `currentTicketId`: Only present if conversation has support ticket
- `media`: Only present for media messages
- `templateData`: Only present for template messages
- `quickReplies`: Only present for messages with quick reply buttons

#### Message Types and Examples

**1. Text Message:**
```json
{
    "recipient": {"id": "201276267641"},
    "message": {"text": "Hello, how can I help you today?"}
}
```

**2. Image Message:**
```json
{
    "recipient": {"id": "201276267641"},
    "media": {
        "contentType": "image/jpeg",
        "url": "https://example.com/image.jpg",
        "size": 150000,
        "name": "product.jpg",
        "mediaType": "Image"
    }
}
```

**3. Template Message:**
```json
{
    "recipient": {"id": "201276267641"},
    "message": {"text": "##hello_template##John##Support##"}
}
```

## Template APIs

### List Templates
**GET** `/template/list`

**Query Parameters:**
- `Name` (string): Filter by template name
- `Status` (string): Filter by status ("APPROVED"|"PENDING"|"REJECTED")
- `Category` (string): Filter by category
- `Page` (number): Page number (default: 1)
- `PageSize` (number): Items per page (default: 10)

### Create or Update Template
**POST** `/template/create-or-update`

**Request Body:**
```json
{
    "template_id": null, // null for create, string for update
    "category": "MARKETING", // "MARKETING"|"UTILITY"|"AUTHENTICATION"
    "name": "template_name",
    "language": "en", // Language code
    "components": [
        {
            "type": "BODY", // "HEADER"|"BODY"|"FOOTER"|"BUTTONS"
            "text": "Hello {{1}}, welcome to {{2}}!",
            "example": {
                "body_text": [["John", "T2 Communicate"]]
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

## Contact Management

### Create Contact
**POST** `/contacts/create`

**Request Body:**
```json
{
    "name": "string", // Required: Contact name
    "phoneNumber": "string", // Required: Valid phone number
    "dynamicFieldsValues": [ // Optional: Custom fields
        {
            "organizationDynamicFieldId": "string",
            "value": "string"
        }
    ],
    "groupIds": ["string"] // Optional: Group memberships
}
```

## Webhook/Callback API

### Overview
Yes, your understanding is correct. T2 system will call your provided callback API to post message status updates and delivery receipts.

### Callback Configuration
You need to provide T2 with your callback endpoint URL. T2 will send HTTP POST requests to this URL whenever message status changes occur.

### Callback Request Structure
T2 will send the following data to your callback URL:

```json
{
    "messageId": "string", // Original message ID from send response
    "conversationId": "string", // Conversation identifier
    "contactNumber": "string", // Recipient phone number
    "status": "string", // New message status
    "timestamp": "2025-08-03T12:18:39.681Z", // Status change time
    "errorCode": "string", // Optional: Error code if failed
    "errorMessage": "string", // Optional: Error description
    "webhookType": "message_status" // Callback type identifier
}
```

### Message Status Values

T2 Communicate webhook callbacks use these exact status values (matching the MessageStatusType constants):

| Status | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Sent` | Message successfully sent to WhatsApp |
| `Delivered` | Message delivered to recipient's device |
| `Read` | Message opened/read by recipient |
| `Failed` | Message delivery failed |
| `InProgress` | Message is being processed |
| `Scheduled` | Message scheduled for future delivery |

### Callback Response Requirements
Your callback endpoint should:
1. Respond with HTTP 200 status for successful processing
2. Respond within 30 seconds
3. Handle duplicate callbacks (implement idempotency)
4. Return non-200 status for retry scenarios

### Example Callback Implementation
```javascript
app.post('/t2-callback', (req, res) => {
    const { messageId, status, contactNumber, timestamp } = req.body;

    // Update message status in your system
    updateMessageStatus(messageId, status);

    // Log the status change
    console.log(`Message ${messageId} to ${contactNumber} is now ${status}`);

    // Respond with success
    res.status(200).json({ received: true });
});
```

